  "text": "The association of lipids and lipoproteins with breast cancer was determined. [CITATION_1] Assessment of serum lipids among breast cancer, by Ghahremanfard et al., revealed highest levels of cholesterol and lipoproteins. [CITATION_2] Thereby, it has been concluded that increased serum lipid levels could have an important role in the progression of cancers in women, including breast and ovarian cancers, while lower level of lipids and lipoproteins may be used as markers for discriminating gastric cancer.",
